<section id="quickstart">
  <h2>First launch</h2>
  <p>Junction opens a short setup the first time you run it.</p>
  <h3>1 · Pick a fallback browser</h3>
  <p>Where anything your rules don't match will open. This is the safety net that makes routing non-destructive — you can add rules gradually and nothing breaks in the meantime.</p>
  <h3>2 · Make Junction your default browser</h3>
  <p>The one step it can't work without: being the default browser is <i>how</i> Junction sees every clicked link. Setup offers to do it, or set it yourself under <b>System Settings → Desktop &amp; Dock → Default web browser</b>. Junction hands each link off to a real browser afterward — you never browse "inside" it.</p>
  <h3>3 · Enable a few starter rules</h3>
  <p>Setup only offers rules for apps and browsers you actually have installed. After that Junction lives in the menu bar; click the icon for recent links, settings, and updates.</p>
  <Note tag="Tip">Hold <b>⌥ Option</b> while clicking any link to force the picker, whatever your rules say.</Note>
</section>
